    "translation":{"eng":"O brothers! Once, at the house of Gaurīdāsa Paṇḍit, Śrī Caitanya, Śrī Nityānanda, and Their devotees, headed by Śrīvāsa Ṭhākura, were relishing [various Bengali sweets such as] luci-cini (white-flour purīs dusted with sugar), kṣīra (sweetened condensed milk), sāra (thick cream), miṭhāi (sweet meats), pāyasa (sweet rice), and piṭhā-pānā (coconut cake rolls in sweetened condensed milk)."}},{
